<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20577] zero copy streaming allocates direct memory that isn&apos;t used, but does help to fragment the memory space</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20577</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is forked from the patch to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20567&quot; title=&quot;SAI marks an index as non-empty when a partial partition/row modifications is flushed due to repair&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20567&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20567&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as it isn&#8217;t related to SAI, so better to isolate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When Zero Copy Streaming creates its per-file writers, it allocates direct memory per file; but this allocation is never used.  This causes issues as the direct memory managed by Cassandra gets fragmented, so we run out of space and OOM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
INFO  [node3_Stream-Deserializer-/127.0.0.1:7012-cf906983] 2025-04-21 21:55:51,613 ERROR 21:55:51 [Stream 13815658-1dd2-11b2-98f1-3dfc14dd20f3] Error &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; reading sstable from stream &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; table = ks1.tbl
java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Cannot reserve 2097152 bytes of direct buffer memory (allocated: 1055235964, limit: 1056309248)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
